bcl:definition.bcl:text:
dog-in-training team means a dog trainer and a dog-in-training
that are working together to train the dog-in-training to become a guide dog or service
dog;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
respecting the conditions, qualifications and requirements that must be met or
            continue to be met by an individual or a dog, or both, as the case may be, for the
            purposes of the issuance or renewal of each type or class of certificate;

for the purposes of section 5 (2) (b), respecting information or documents that
            must be included in or accompany an application for the issuance or renewal of a
            certificate;

imposing requirements on guide dog teams, service dog teams or dog-in-training
            teams respecting the carrying, producing or displaying of a certificate or evidence of
            certification under this Act;
